  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cyclone Falcon Flash Flood Food NEMP Response</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">As an initial response, ADRA Philippines will distribute emergency food packs to 637 affected households, prioritizing the most vulnerable affected families at the evacuation center.

&#x2022;	Beneficiaries will receive food packets containing 10 kilos of rice, 3 canned sardines, 3 can of tuna, 3 packs of noodles, 3 packs of pancit canton, 1 liter of oil, 1 kg of mung bean, 24 sachets of cereal drink and 1 kilo of peanuts. Food items are contained in one pack following the Sphere standards for individual energy requirement. Each food pack will last to 5 days for a family with 5 members.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022;	Typhoon Falcon &#x2013; 6th typhoon to hit the Philippines in 2019
&#x2022;	Since July 16, severe rains have resulted in flash flooding in at least five towns in Lanao del Norte in Northern Mindanao.
&#x2022;	A landslide was already reported
&#x2022;	Authorities are helping citizens evacuate from the flood prone towns of Kapatagan, Lala, Sultan Naga Dimaporo, Sapad and Tubod.
&#x2022;	An estimated 6,000 residents are affected and temporarily evacuated in gymnasiums and community halls</narrative>
  </description>
